tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Renal function is impaired, as indicated by significantly elevated creatinine. Alkaline phosphatase is mildly elevated, which may suggest cholestasis or bone turnover; liver transaminases are within or below normal. Other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, proteins, and lipids, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal and hepatobiliary function.
